surf (0.4.1-6) unstable; urgency=low

  This release of surf fixes ~/.surf directory permission vulnerability
  CVE-2012-0842 reported in #659296. If you are upgrading from a previous
  version of surf you should consider manually changing permission of ~/.surf
  directory from 0755 to 0700 using chmod. If this is a fresh install of surf
  you can ignore this message.

 -- Vasudev Kamath <kamathvasudev@gmail.com>  Fri, 10 Feb 2012 23:43:16 +0530

